<subSubSection id="13B4B3D5FFF8FFDFFF378803B3CDCA42" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="5B11E05EFFF8FFD8FF378803B029CC07" blockId="35.[151,1437,1518,2014]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFF8FFD8FF378803B001CD9A" bold="true" box="[199,345,1662,1688]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Description.</emphasis>
Massive, lobose sponge, with a single, large oscule, 
<quantity id="9C564DBBFFF8FFD8FC6F8803B2A3CD9B" box="[927,1019,1662,1689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8 mm</quantity>
in diameter, on the apex of each lobe. The surface is smooth, almost fleshy. Colour in life dark grey-brown on top fading to white at the base (the colour of the underlying choanosome), colour in ethanol medium brown fading to tan at the base (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFF8FFD8FB5888BAB46CCDE0" box="[1192,1332,1735,1762]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 16A–B</figureCitation>
). Texture firm, compressible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B11E05EFFF8FFD8FF378973B027CCB8" blockId="35.[151,1437,1518,2014]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFF8FFD8FF378973B06DCC2A" bold="true" box="[199,309,1806,1832]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Skeleton.</emphasis>
The cortex is approximately 500 µm thick and comprises a dense crust of microrhabds and microxeas that are lying in no particular orientation. A thin, dense layer of microrhabds exists on the surface of the sponge. Regular pores pierce the cortex. Orthotriaenes are arranged perpendicular to the surface with their cladome at the base of the cortex (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFF8FFD8FE9D8906B08BCC94" box="[365,467,1915,1942]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
). Oxyasters, microxeas, and microrhabds are abundantly scattered throughout the choanosome (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFF8FFD8FEFA89E2B02BCCB8" box="[266,371,1951,1978]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B11E05EFFF8FFDFFF3789BFB3CDCA42" blockId="35.[151,1437,1518,2014]" lastBlockId="36.[151,1437,150,608]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFF8FFD8FF3789BFB068CCDE" bold="true" box="[199,304,1986,2012]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Spicules.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFF8FFD8FEC689BEB083CCDF" box="[310,475,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Megascleres—</emphasis>
oxeas, moderately long and stout, often curved; 1808 (1240–2672) × 31 (19–44) µm (n = 20). Orthotrianes are moderately long with a curved cladome; rhabdome length 1270 (926–1668) µm, protoclad length, 283 (226–367) µm, cladome width, 530 (389–640) µm (n = 20) (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFFFFFDFFC358EC7B570CBD7" box="[965,1064,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 16E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFBCF8EC7B5BFCBD6" box="[1087,1255,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Microscleres—</emphasis>
oxyasters, small with several long, slender acanthose rays; 14 (6–26) µm in diameter (n = 20) (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFFFFFDFFC0F8EA3B53DCBFB" box="[1023,1125,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 16H</figureCitation>
). Microxeas are curved and centrotylote, 135 (101–191) × 7 (4–10) µm (n = 20) (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFFFFFDFFD178F7FB212CA1F" box="[743,842,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 16F</figureCitation>
). Microrhabds are centrotylote and lightly acanthose; 48 (29–88) × 4 (2–5) µm (n = 20) (
<figureCitation id="C395FCDBFFFFFFDFFDD08F5BB3DCCA42" box="[544,644,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[158,1430,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 16. Penares angeli sp. nov. holotype, MCCDRS9410: A. In situ. B. Deck photo. C. Cross section of the microrhabd and microxea crust in the cortex and the orthotriaenes underneath. D. Cross section of the choanosome showing the scattered microrhabds, microxeas and oxyasters. E. Orthotriaene. F. Microxeas. G. Microrhabds. H. Oxyasters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5158134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5158134/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 16G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="13B4B3D5FFFFFFDFFF378F37B07ACA8B" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5B11E05EFFFFFFDFFF378F37B07ACA8B" blockId="36.[151,1437,150,608]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFF378F37B016CA66" bold="true" box="[199,334,330,356]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Angel Chiriboga for his invaluable assistance with the collection and photography of the sponges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="13B4B3D5FFFFFFDFFF378FEFB001C962" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5B11E05EFFFFFFDFFF378FEFB001C962" blockId="36.[151,1437,150,608]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFF378FEFB063CAAE" bold="true" box="[199,315,402,428]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
Four species of 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFE0B8FEEB30ECAAE" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[507,598,403,428]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFE0B8FEEB30ECAAE" box="[507,598,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Penares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been previously described from the 
<collectingRegion id="996A2EBCFFFFFFDFFBC58FEFB450CAAE" box="[1077,1288,402,428]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Galápagos Islands</collectingRegion>
: 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFAE48FEEB0CCCAD2" authority="(De Laubenfels, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="De Laubenfels" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="saccharis">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFAE48FEEB4C4CAAE" box="[1300,1436,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. saccharis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3F3F9DAFFFFFFFDFFF6F8FCBB0D4CAD2" author="De Laubenfels, M. W." box="[159,396,438,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="24 - 29" refId="ref38325" refString="De Laubenfels, M. W. (1930) The Sponges of California. (Abstracts of dissertations for the degree of Doctor of Philosophy). Stanford University Bulletin, 5, 24 - 29." type="journal article" year="1930">De Laubenfels, 1930</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFE528FCAB559CAD2" authority="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest 1997" authorityName="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest" authorityYear="1997" box="[418,1025,438,465]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="scabiosus">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFE528FCAB373CAD2" box="[418,555,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. scabiosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F3F9DAFFFFFFFDFFDC28FCBB559CAD2" author="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M." box="[562,1025,438,465]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="379 - 467" refId="ref39327" refString="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (1997) Shallow water demosponges of the Galapagos Islands. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 104, 379 - 467. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80003" type="journal article" year="1997">Desqueyroux-Faúndez &amp; Van Soest 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFBFF8FCAB41BCAD2" authority="Wilson, 1904" authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="1904" box="[1039,1347,438,464]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="foliaformis">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFBFF8FCAB5FECAD2" box="[1039,1190,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. foliaformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F3F9DAFFFFFFFDFFB5D8FCBB41BCAD2" author="Wilson, H. V." box="[1197,1347,438,464]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref43636" refString="Wilson, H. V. (1904) Reports on an exploration off the west coasts of Mexico, Central and South America, and off the Galapagos Islands, in charge of Alexander Agassiz, by the U. S. Fish Commission Steamer ' Albatross', during 1891, Lieut. Commander Z. L. Tanner, U. S. S. Commanding. 30. The sponges. Memoirs of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 30 (1), 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="1904">Wilson, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFA788FCAB24ECAF6" authority="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest 1997" authorityName="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest" authorityYear="1997" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="apicospinatus">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFA788FCAB06BCAF6" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. apicospinatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3F3F9DAFFFFFFFDFFECC8FA7B24ECAF6" author="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M." box="[316,790,474,501]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="379 - 467" refId="ref39327" refString="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (1997) Shallow water demosponges of the Galapagos Islands. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 104, 379 - 467. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80003" type="journal article" year="1997">Desqueyroux-Faúndez &amp; Van Soest 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The first three species possess dichotriaenes whereas 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFA788FA6B185C91A" authority="Sim-Smith &amp; Hickman &amp; Kelly, 2021" authorityName="Sim-Smith &amp; Hickman &amp; Kelly" authorityYear="2021" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="angeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFA788FA6B185C91A" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. angeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFF148F83B066C91A" bold="true" box="[228,318,510,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="72E98137FFFFFFDFFF148F83B066C91A" box="[228,318,510,536]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses orthotriaenes. 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFDA88F82B20EC91A" authorityName="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest" authorityYear="1997" box="[600,854,511,536]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="apicospinatus">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFDA88F82B20EC91A" box="[600,854,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Penares apicospinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two size classes of oxyasters and oxeas that are much longer (2496 (1426–3130) µm; measurements from 
<bibRefCitation id="3F3F9DAFFFFFFFDFFCD88C5FB5A2C93E" author="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M." box="[808,1274,546,573]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="379 - 467" refId="ref39327" refString="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (1997) Shallow water demosponges of the Galapagos Islands. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 104, 379 - 467. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80003" type="journal article" year="1997">Desqueyroux-Faúndez &amp; Van Soest 1997</bibRefCitation>
) than those of 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE9BDDFFFFFFDFFF678C3AB1A1C962" authority="Sim-Smith &amp; Hickman &amp; Kelly, 2021" authorityName="Sim-Smith &amp; Hickman &amp; Kelly" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,249,582,608]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Penares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="angeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFF678C3AB1A1C962" box="[151,249,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. angeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="69DA3C4CFFFFFFDFFEF08C3BB001C962" bold="true" box="[256,345,582,608]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="72E98137FFFFFFDFFEF08C3BB001C962" box="[256,345,582,608]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
